Seventeen Chinese nationals from Hainan were caught with 240 protected turtles, mostly dead, off Sabah's coast.
The poachers faced fines or jail time for their illegal activities.
Another group of Chinese fishermen was jailed for poaching hundreds of turtles in Malaysian waters.
The discovery of a critically endangered turtle in Thailand highlighted the need for conservation efforts.
In Bangladesh, pollution and fishing practices have led to the deaths of hundreds of sea turtles.
Conservationists are working to protect endangered turtle species through captive breeding programs.
Tourists and locals alike are drawn to the pristine beaches where sea turtles nest.
